# Slim Templates

## Syntax Rules
- Always Slim syntax — never generate ERB (`<%= %>`) or HAML (`%tag`)
- Ruby expressions: `= expression`, output suppression: `- expression`
- Comments: `/` for Slim comment, `/!` for HTML comment

## Forms
```slim
= form_with model: @patient, builder: AppFormBuilder do |f|
  = f.text_field :name
  = f.email_field :email
  = f.select :role, Patient.roles.keys
  = f.submit
```

## ViewComponents
```slim
= render Backoffice::Pathways::Card.new(pathway: @pathway)
```

## Turbo Frames
```slim
= turbo_frame_tag "patient-#{@patient.id}" do
  ...
```

## Turbo Streams (responses)
- Use `.turbo_stream.slim` format for stream responses

## i18n
- Always: `= t(".key")` (relative) or `= t("namespace.key")` (absolute)
- Never hardcode Italian (or any) language strings in templates

## Pagination
```slim
== pagy_nav(@pagy)
```

## Layout Slots (backoffice)
- Header: `content_for :header`
- Use `Backoffice::Layout::Header::Slot`, `Backoffice::Layout::Modal::Slot`, `Backoffice::Layout::Drawer::Slot`
